text: Albert François Lebrun (; 29 August 1871 – 6 March 1950) was a French politician. He was the President of France from 1932 to 1940. He was the last president of the Third Republic. ==References== Category:1871 births Category:1950 deaths Category:Presidents of the Senate (France) Category:Presidents of France Category:Deaths from pneumonia Category:Politicians from Grand Est Category:People from Meurthe-et-Moselle Category:20th-century presidents of France
